Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.02,0:01:43.97,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Matsue Castle
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.16,0:01:47.27,Def_up,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a day in autumn, we were at Matsue in Shimane Prefecture on a trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.27,0:01:51.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At the Matsue hot springs, we met 5 members in a group doing a linked verse trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.77,0:01:55.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,On the following day, one of the members,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.49,0:01:59.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ushikubo Gozou-san, was murdered in front of Matsue Castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.03,0:02:02.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,With the index finger on his right hand extended,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.16,0:02:03.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,a mysterious message was left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.83,0:02:10.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit is probably among the remaining four members.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.17,0:02:13.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Linked verse contest, it's a showdown!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.42,0:02:20.10,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,The 14th Round of Matsue Tamatsukuri Linked Verse Contest
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.42,0:02:20.10,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.11,0:02:24.11,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Tamatsukuri Hot Springs
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.12,0:02:27.25,Signs,,0,0,0,,Tamatsukuri Shirasuna Inn
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.93,0:02:24.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And we shall now commence with our gathering.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.10,0:02:29.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This time we will be reciting a total of 14 linked verses.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.44,0:02:33.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And to make it easy for our guest, Mouri-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.86,0:02:35.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We shall recite in a Shiritori manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.23,0:02:38.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shiritori is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.24,0:02:41.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, you only have to follow a few rules,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.45,0:02:42.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but besides that, you can do anything you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.53,0:02:47.07,Def_up,,0000,0000,0000,,First, we shall begin with an opening verse with 5, 7 and 5 syllables,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.07,0:02:52.29,Def_up,,0000,0000,0000,,And then with two lines of 7 and 7 syllables, then one of 5, 7 and 5, and keep repeating the pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.97,0:02:51.29,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Andou Reiko (43)\NJunior College Assistant Professor \NDeprtment of Japanese Literature
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.46,0:02:56.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But please, be careful to not link your verse to the second one before, called Uchikoshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.54,0:03:01.22,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Shiina Ryousuke (38)\NDentist
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.92,0:03:01.22,Def_up,,0000,0000,0000,,Also please try to include the four seasons in the 14 verses.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.27,0:03:05.18,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Yagisawa Takumi (32)\NJapanese Confectionery Shop Owner
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.64,0:03:05.18,Def_up,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides that, the first verse will be about the moon, the second and third one, about love,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.22,0:03:09.14,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Kawaguchi Mizuki (27)\NLibrarian
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.56,0:03:07.90,Def_up,,0000,0000,0000,,then the 13th verse should be one with flowers as a theme...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.90,0:03:11.80,Def_up,,0000,0000,0000,,And the final verse, should be a Spring theme to end on a happy note.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.80,0:03:13.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.31,0:03:14.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.57,0:03:18.40,Def_it,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey, are you alright old man?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.24,0:03:21.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we'll give the actual recitation a try.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.78,0:03:25.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,First, the hokku (first verse). The verses you all wrote are,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.74,0:03:27.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,for Shiina-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.33,0:03:30.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Even the gods, gather to look through the window at a deer".
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.75,0:03:32.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yagisawa-san's verse reads,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.25,0:03:35.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"The praying mantis is raising a hatchet over the big turtle"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.25,0:03:37.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Miauki-san's is,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.63,0:03:40.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"The flame that singed the tender trees dances in autumn colors"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.68,0:03:43.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And Ushikubo-san's verse,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.80,0:03:47.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Autumn surges, there's no sorrow in my life".
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.22,0:03:53.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,These are all fine verses, but since the reason for this gathering was to ease Ushikubo-san's regret.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.10,0:03:55.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I think we should begin with his verse.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.15,0:03:57.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.61,0:04:03.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then would somebody start off with the "waki"?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.41,0:04:07.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is "Waki"?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.12,0:04:09.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That is the second verse.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.08,0:04:11.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It is composed with a seasonal word related to the season in the opening verse.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.87,0:04:17.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"In the midst oof silence, a fruit now falls".
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.84,0:04:21.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, it's a good verse proceeding with an honest acceptance of the opening one.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.22,0:04:24.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next is Yagisawa-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.05,0:04:24.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.26,0:04:30.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, will father be able to add a good one?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.23,0:04:35.39,Def_it,,0000,0000,0000,,Expecting him to have any aesthetics is a long shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.44,0:04:42.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I've finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.03,0:04:45.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"In the moonlight, your next verse would be about Dracula".
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.24,0:04:53.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How interesting. To use such an extreme character as Dracula is refreshing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.87,0:04:56.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me. Is that acceptable?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.37,0:05:00.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes the third verse can be recited wholeheartedly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.09,0:05:02.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,From here on, just let your imagination soar.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.17,0:05:05.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Imagination soar!?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.80,0:05:08.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, it's Mizuki-san's turn right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.05,0:05:10.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.18,0:05:12.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Texts are made in Japan".
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.21,0:05:18.31,TL Note,,0000,0000,0000,,"Textbooks are made in Japan".
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.02,0:05:18.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,For that, instead of "texts", it would be better to use "textbooks", wouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.69,0:05:20.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It would have more words, but that doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.77,0:05:21.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.03,0:05:23.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mouri-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.24,0:05:29.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you try composing one too? It's a shiritori, so please start with "pan" or "han".
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.16,0:05:33.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.84,0:05:43.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This should do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.84,0:05:47.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"The culprit, will be revealed by the famous detective".
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.31,0:05:54.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Something like that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.98,0:06:00.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well about that, the use of "famous detective" registers in the same category as "Dracula".
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.11,0:06:03.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It leaves an impression of reverting back, but that should be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.69,0:06:07.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, I'm next.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.03,0:06:13.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"The destination that we will arrive at, is the eye of a needle of God's knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.08,0:06:18.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As expected of Reiko-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.04,0:06:21.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Gently discarded the famed detective's enthusiasm.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.59,0:06:23.88,Def_it,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not letting this end so quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.25,0:06:26.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I shall recite the next one then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.59,0:06:35.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The anthropoid ape, its face looks just like the child by its side.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.31,0:06:39.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's amusing, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.64,0:06:41.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We, the seven people here, need some pleasant moments in our life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.61,0:06:44.15,Def_it,,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.11,0:06:52.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yagisawa-san. Here you go. It was at the lobby earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.57,0:06:56.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm such an idiot. I dropped it again? Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.16,0:06:56.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.50,0:07:03.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.17,0:07:06.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone's doing very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.59,0:07:08.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How is it, Mouri-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.80,0:07:11.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm completely clueless.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.18,0:07:14.22,Def_it,,0000,0000,0000,,Only 3 verses remaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.22,0:07:16.43,Def_it,,0000,0000,0000,,If I don't get a breakthrough in the case around now then...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.60,0:07:19.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mizuki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.27,0:07:24.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You said that you composed the verse earlier about autumn colors at the rest area in the samurai mansions, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.44,0:07:25.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.48,0:07:28.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.07,0:07:33.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I went to the samurai mansions earlier but I couldn't see the autumn colors from the rest area though.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.03,0:07:36.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that true, Conan?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.24,0:07:36.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.74,0:07:41.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible that I saw the autumn colors from a different place.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.16,0:07:42.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A different place?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.46,0:07:43.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where would that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.63,0:07:49.80,Def_it,,0000,0000,0000,,Is Mizuki-san the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.01,0:07:54.43,Def_it,,0000,0000,0000,,But if she isn't, why did she lie?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.64,0:08:03.64,Def_it,,0000,0000,0000,,Could this verse possibly be...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.69,0:08:07.02,Def_it,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, Mizuki-san must have done this for his sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.73,0:08:11.11,Def_it,,0000,0000,0000,,Moreover, what does that dying message mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.37,0:08:22.04,Def_it,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's what it means.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.04,0:08:25.37,Def_it,,0000,0000,0000,,But, why did that person do such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.88,0:08:31.26,Def_it,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.26,0:08:32.84,Def_it,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what it was!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.63,0:08:35.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Mouri-san wants me to?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.89,0:08:40.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. He said to keep it secret from Inspector Yasugi-san and have Tsubaki-san investigate instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.68,0:08:42.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.61,0:08:50.36,Def_it,,0000,0000,0000,,If my instincts are right...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.36,0:08:53.03,Def_it,,0000,0000,0000,,the culprit is most likely, that person.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.79,0:09:01.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I've figure it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.16,0:09:05.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What exactly did you figure out?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.00,0:09:07.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The deceased Mr.Ushikubo's dying message.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.46,0:09:14.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,His finger wasn't pointing the bamboos. But rather, something else that was before it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.72,0:09:16.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Something else before it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.59,0:09:22.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Something through the thicket that surrounds the promenade, further ahead across the canal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.85,0:09:28.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. That's where Mizuki-san composed her peom, it's the samurai mansions.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.15,0:09:31.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the culprit is you, Mizuki-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.40,0:09:33.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.12,0:09:39.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mizuki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.62,0:09:43.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The tenth verse is about love isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.70,0:09:45.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In addition, it's on unrequited love.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.12,0:09:50.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That reminds me, didn't you play the reed pipe during dinner last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.50,0:09:51.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.96,0:09:58.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it. Mizuki-san unrequited love is Yagisawa-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.55,0:10:02.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. That's why last night Mizuki-san was...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.72,0:10:04.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What happend last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.85,0:10:08.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ushikubo-san said horrible things to Yagisawa-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.90,0:10:11.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And Mizuki-san was looking at them worriedly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.15,0:10:15.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait a minute... That means...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.40,0:10:18.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. I got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.53,0:10:22.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mizuki-san! You were sticking up for Yagisawa-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.62,0:10:27.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, Mouri-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.96,0:10:33.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, Mizuki-san was worried about the matter between Mr.Ushikubo and Yagisawa-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.96,0:10:38.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She changed her plans and met with Ushikubo-san at Matsue castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.59,0:10:41.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And that moment, what she saw was...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.23,0:10:53.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's not it. I didn't see anything like that. I just...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.07,0:10:55.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just what?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.78,0:10:57.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mizuki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.20,0:11:01.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mizuki-san. It's better to answer them truthfully.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.99,0:11:03.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.16,0:11:05.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you shoud too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.29,0:11:08.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for sounding so impertinent.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.37,0:11:15.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, if you really like that person... and really care about him then you should.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.68,0:11:20.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.68,0:11:24.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't going to Matsue castle, but instead, I was heading to Gesshoji.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.10,0:11:27.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was worried about Yagisawa-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.02,0:11:32.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But on my way there, the bus to Matsue castle passed mine and,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.31,0:11:36.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw Yagisawa-san in that bus.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.07,0:11:42.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I set off for Matsue castle immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.66,0:11:45.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But when I got to the promenade,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.12,0:11:48.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ushikubo-san had already passed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.33,0:11:52.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And a little way from his extended finger there was...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.09,0:12:01.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After that I hurried back to the Samurai mansions, and I tried to calm down at the rest area.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.43,0:12:05.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then it was time to meet back and I returned to the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.80,0:12:10.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Please hold on. It's true that I went to Matsue castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.06,0:12:11.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I didn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.69,0:12:13.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't even go to the promenade.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.48,0:12:15.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then where in Matsue castle did you go to?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.77,0:12:17.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At Jozan Inari Shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.57,0:12:20.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's where a lot of fox statues are, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.32,0:12:24.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was asked by Ushikubo-san to meet there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.28,0:12:28.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was at Gensshoji for about 30 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.91,0:12:31.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When Ushikubo-san sent me a text message on my cellphone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.96,0:12:34.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It says, " Come immediately to the Inari temple at Matsue castle".
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.46,0:12:43.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was about 5 minutes past 10 when I got to the temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.18,0:12:48.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After that I waited for 15 minutes, Ushikubo-san didn't show up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.43,0:12:50.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And I couldn't get through to his phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.98,0:12:54.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,With no other choice, I returned to Gesshoji,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.77,0:12:56.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and composed my verse on the big turtle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.19,0:13:01.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's the case, why was your eye medication at the crime scene?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.61,0:13:02.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.49,0:13:05.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's the truth, Police officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.82,0:13:09.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you think I'm lying, pleses check Ushikubo-san's cellphone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.45,0:13:12.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We have checked all the records on his cellphone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.08,0:13:16.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A record of the text message you mentioned wasn't there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.42,0:13:18.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.00,0:13:19.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What about his reserve phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.38,0:13:24.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ushikubo-san said he has a spare phone in his bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.17,0:13:28.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We've checked through all his luggage, and there was only one cellphone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.68,0:13:37.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yagisawa-san, sure you didn't steal Ushikubo-san's reserve phone and sent yourself a text message?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.81,0:13:39.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.40,0:13:41.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Yasugi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.73,0:13:44.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We found the murder weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.36,0:13:45.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.36,0:13:48.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was thrown in the Gesshoji pond.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.62,0:13:52.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The special police department examined this raincoat
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.65,0:13:55.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and found some blood identical to the victim's blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.62,0:13:57.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And on this raincoat...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.25,0:14:00.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yagisawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.00,0:14:02.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This settles it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.75,0:14:04.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.97,0:14:07.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we continue this at the station?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.47,0:14:10.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do it, detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.68,0:14:12.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This must be a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.06,0:14:13.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yagisawa-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.41,0:14:35.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What an unbelievable linked verse contest this has turned ot to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.33,0:14:39.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's end here for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.00,0:14:41.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.22,0:14:50.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, let me recite the next verse.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.51,0:14:53.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I begin with the "chi" sound, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.06,0:14:59.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Done.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.48,0:15:01.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Chocolate cakes, quickly give them to me".
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.82,0:15:07.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That won't do. That doesn't cut it as a linked verse.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.24,0:15:07.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.86,0:15:12.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,From this point, you can associate ideas about chocolate cakes, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.32,0:15:14.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a child-like fun verse.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.87,0:15:16.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next is a verse with flowers theme, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.87,0:15:18.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shiina-san, please form one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.12,0:15:20.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.21,0:15:21.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a verse that starts with "i" sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.17,0:15:23.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Compose a beautiful verse.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.00,0:15:25.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.80,0:15:29.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm done.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.26,0:15:34.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Someday, my daughter and I will go to temple with flowers".
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.10,0:15:36.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.01,0:15:37.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.93,0:15:39.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.27,0:15:44.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That verse was the same as the one Uncle Mouri recited to me earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.36,0:15:45.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.61,0:15:52.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Father, when did you compose that verse?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.70,0:15:54.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.70,0:16:00.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,oh-no-this-is bad...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.88,0:16:04.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Father?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.63,0:16:08.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran, actually that verse wasn't composed by me,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.76,0:16:14.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The man we met at the lobby yesterday, Tomonaga-san from the business district composed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.56,0:16:21.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That was what Mr. Ushikubo had written in his notebook.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.31,0:16:28.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shiina-san, you were certain that it was a verse that Ushikubo-san composed weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.15,0:16:32.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You could not forgive the fact that such a crude man could compose such a beautiful verse.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.95,0:16:36.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you tore it out from his notebook, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.12,0:16:38.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Aftre murdering Mr. Ushikubo.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.41,0:16:46.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You added codes in the verses that you recited.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.09,0:16:51.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The 7th word from the 7th verse, 9th word of the 9th verse,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.09,0:16:54.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the 11th word from the 11th verse. It says
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.64,0:17:02.80,TL Note,,0000,0000,0000,,I am the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.64,0:16:58.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I am the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.31,0:17:02.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And then, you recited provoking verses while subconsciously confessing that it was you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.77,0:17:06.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Adding your message in your verses,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.56,0:17:10.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,ridiculing both me and the police, chuckling away.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.19,0:17:15.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Judging from that part of your personality, I thought that with the appropriate conditions,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.91,0:17:22.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you would definitely recite the verse stolen from Mr. Ushikubo, as your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.66,0:17:27.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,With the simple reason that you really like this verse.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.84,0:17:31.71,Def_past,,0000,0000,0000,,I like verses with emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.71,0:17:34.09,Def_past,,0000,0000,0000,,Like the love of a father for his daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.09,0:17:41.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the required conditions were, having Yagisawa-san taken into custody as the suspect,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.81,0:17:47.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and connecting the 13th verse on flowers from the verse prior to it in shiritori manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.81,0:17:50.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And was that the verse you told Conan about earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.32,0:17:58.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I had predicted, you read the verse you stole from Ushikubo-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.37,0:18:01.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As if to personally display your victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.66,0:18:05.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The codes in the verses were just a prank, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.66,0:18:10.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Moreover, last night Ushikubo-san had shown me the verse I just recited.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.59,0:18:13.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on a minute, I have an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.42,0:18:14.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alibi?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.55,0:18:15.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.47,0:18:19.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Around 10:05 when I was at the English Park in Teien Art Museum,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.76,0:18:25.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,a lady on duty found the parents of a lost boy. I just remembered this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.81,0:18:31.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can know something like that easily by setting up some video cameras,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.23,0:18:32.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That was under the hedge.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.03,0:18:37.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan found some tripod marks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.57,0:18:41.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You had gone to Teien Art Museum in the morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.08,0:18:44.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and set up a video camera by the pond.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.08,0:18:51.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,With Mr. Ushikubo's spare cellphone that you had stolen, you sent a text message to Yagisawa-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.34,0:18:57.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you went to Matsue castle and murdered Ushikubo-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.51,0:19:03.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, you placed Yagisawa-san's eye medication near Ushikubo-san's finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.81,0:19:06.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then throw the raincoat and the murder weapon at Gesshoji.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.64,0:19:09.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Retrived the video from Teien Art Museum.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.27,0:19:13.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And nonchalantly you returned to the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.82,0:19:16.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's quite an interesting deduction, Mouri-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.86,0:19:18.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But unfortunately...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.45,0:19:20.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you are talking about proof, I have some.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.03,0:19:23.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ushikubo-san's dying message.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.78,0:19:29.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That wasn't pointing to the bamboo, nor to the samurai's mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.04,0:19:31.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The message was the number, '1'.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.46,0:19:34.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.21,0:19:38.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran, what was the first verse of linked verse called again?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.38,0:19:39.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hokku?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.09,0:19:43.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, Detective Tsubaki, what is the result of your observation?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.22,0:19:43.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.93,0:19:48.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,From these shoes of Mr.Shiina. On the left foot, topmost left hook, we confirmed
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.31,0:19:53.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr.Ushikubo's streched bloody index finger fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.65,0:20:03.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, his dying message was the hook on your shoe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.70,0:20:08.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your heart was probably taken in by the verse in Mr.Ushikubo notebook,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.95,0:20:12.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and didn't notice him touching the hook on your shoe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.25,0:20:15.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I lose, Mouri-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.30,0:20:18.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I killed Ushikubo.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.96,0:20:21.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, why did you suspect me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.72,0:20:26.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My first suspiction were when you were drawing a lots last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.06,0:20:30.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, the one who created the lots would draw last.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.18,0:20:32.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, you went on the second draw.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.02,0:20:36.02,Def_past,,0000,0000,0000,,Next, according to age line up, will be my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.86,0:20:42.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You manipulated the lots at that time for Mr.Ushikubo to pick an easy place to be murdered,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.45,0:20:46.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and gave yourself the furthest location where you could create your alibi easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.29,0:20:53.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As expected of Japan's best detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.04,0:20:57.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The motive for killing Mr.Ushikubo must be...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.25,0:21:02.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, for tricking us out of our money, I just couldn't forgive him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.55,0:21:05.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even then, you do not have the right to pass judgment on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.80,0:21:07.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.43,0:21:10.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.35,0:21:15.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The only one who can pass judgment on him is God.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.82,0:21:24.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And for the sake of telling me that, the God in Izumo must have called you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.33,0:22:58.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.01,0:23:03.00,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Nagatama Bridge
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.38,0:23:03.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mizuki-san's feelings seem to have reached Yagisawa-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.00,0:23:05.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.01,0:23:06.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, Reiko sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.84,0:23:09.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's one verse left for the linked verses.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.30,0:23:15.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, from my feelings of gratitude for Mouri-san and a greeting to Matsue,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.85,0:23:20.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Lafcadio Hearn, the spring of his smile".
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.19,0:23:22.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's wouderful verse!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.82,0:23:24.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right father?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.07,0:23:25.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.90,0:23:27.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,L-af-ca-?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.70,0:23:29.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Lafcadio Hearn.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.74,0:23:31.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's Koizumi Yakumo, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.62,0:23:33.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Koizumi...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.21,0:23:43.13,Def_it,,0000,0000,0000,,With that, it's more like,"Lafcadio Hearn, the spring of his amazement".
